%sh
# download zip file to local file system, unzip it, and copy it to HDFS
sudo mkdir /data/tmp/strava
sudo chown zeppelin /data/tmp/strava
cd /data/tmp/strava
rm *.gpx
rm activities.zip
echo "donwloading activities.zip"
hadoop fs -get swift://journeyC.default/strava/raw/zip/DBAYARD.zip activities.zip
echo "unzipping"
unzip -q activities.zip
ls -l | head
echo "uploading individual activity files"
hadoop fs -mkdir -p strava/raw/DBAYARD
hadoop fs -put *.gpx strava/raw/DBAYARD/
hadoop fs -ls strava/raw/DBAYARD/ | head 
echo "done"

paragraphs.title: Define function to calculate speed between data points
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
#https://github.com/larsbkrogvig/strava-spark/blob/master/py/preprocessing.ipynb
from pyspark.sql import Window, DataFrame
from pyspark.sql.functions import coalesce, concat, lag, lit, lower, sum, unix_timestamp, max, min, \
                                  sin, cos, atan, sqrt, atan2, radians, degrees, round, avg, first, expr, row_number, when, lpad
#read df from scala
df = DataFrame(z.get("myScalaDataFrame"), sqlContext)

# Timestamp in seconds
df = df.withColumn( 
    'TIME_unix_time', 
    unix_timestamp(df['time'], "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss'Z'")
)

# Partitioning on <athlete> and <activity_name>
window = Window.partitionBy('athlete', 'activityName', 'activityType').orderBy('TIME_unix_time')

def calculate_speed(df, window):
    
    # use the haversine equation: https://www.movable-type.co.uk/scripts/latlong.html
    
    # Time difference in seconds between tracking point and previous tracking point
    df = df.withColumn(
        'TIME_unix_time_diff',
        df['TIME_unix_time'] - lag('TIME_unix_time', count=1).over(window)
    )

    # Latitude and longditude in radians
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_latR',
        radians(df['lat'])
    )
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_lonR',
        radians(df['lon'])
    )
    
    # Latitude and longditude in previous tracking point
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_latR_prev',
        lag('DIST_latR', count=1).over(window)
    )
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_lonR_prev',
        lag('DIST_lonR', count=1).over(window)
    )
    
    # Difference in latitude and longditude since previous tracking point
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_latR_diff',
        coalesce(df['DIST_latR'] - df['DIST_latR_prev'], lit(0))
    )
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_lonR_diff',
        coalesce(df['DIST_lonR'] - df['DIST_lonR_prev'], lit(0))
    )

    # Havesine distance calculation between two tracking points
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_a',
        sin(df['DIST_latR_diff']/2) * sin(df['DIST_latR_diff']/2)
        + cos(df['DIST_latR']) * cos(df['DIST_latR_prev'])
        * sin(df['DIST_lonR_diff']/2) * sin(df['DIST_lonR_diff']/2)
    )
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_c',
        2 * atan2(sqrt(df['DIST_a']), sqrt(1 - df['DIST_a']))
    )
    
    R = 6371000 # Earth radius = 6371000 meters.  http://whatis.techtarget.com/definition/Earths-mean-radius
    
    # Distance between consecutive points
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_diff_meters',
        coalesce(R * df['DIST_c'], lit(0))
    )
    
    # Momentary speed in km/h
    # 3.6 is 60minutes*60seconds divided by 1000m per KM
    df = df.withColumn(
        'SPEED_kmh',
        coalesce(
            3.6 * df['DIST_diff_meters'] / df['TIME_unix_time_diff'],
            lit(0)
        )
    )
    
    df = df.withColumn("SPEED_mph",
      expr("SPEED_kmh * 0.621371"))

    # also calculate initial bearing: https://www.movable-type.co.uk/scripts/latlong.html
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_y',
        sin(df['DIST_lonR_diff']) * cos(df['DIST_latR'])
    )
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_x',
        cos(df['DIST_latR_prev']) * sin(df['DIST_latR']) - sin(df['DIST_latR_prev'])*cos(df['DIST_latR'])*cos(df['DIST_lonR_diff'])
    )
    
    df = df.withColumn(
        'DIST_bearing',
        (degrees(atan2(df['DIST_y'], df['DIST_x']))+360) % 360
    )
    

    return df

paragraphs.title: Calculate speed.  Eliminate data points where it appears you are moving very slowly
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
df = calculate_speed(df, window)

pause_threshold_minutes = 0.5
rest_speed_threshold_kmh = {
    'Ride': 3,
    'Run': 2
}

for atype in rest_speed_threshold_kmh:
    df = df.filter( ~((df['activityType']==atype) & (df['SPEED_kmh']<rest_speed_threshold_kmh[atype])))

# Time difference in seconds between tracking point and previous tracking point
df = df.withColumn(
    'TIME_unix_time_diff',
    df['TIME_unix_time'] - lag('TIME_unix_time', count=1).over(window)
)

paragraphs.title: Break up the activity into blocks whenever you are stopped for a bit
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
# Indicator (0,1) of whether time difference is greater than threshold (new activity block)
df = df.withColumn(
    'BLOCK_isnew',
    coalesce(
        (df['TIME_unix_time_diff'] >= pause_threshold_minutes * 60).cast('integer'),
        lit(0)
    )
)

# Sequence number of activity block per athlete and activity 
df = df.withColumn(
    'BLOCK_seqnum', 
    sum('BLOCK_isnew').over(window)
)

# Activity block id "<athlete>_<activityName>_<integer>"
df = df.withColumn(
    'BLOCK_id',
    concat(
        df['athlete'],
        lit('_'),
        lower(df['activityName']),
        lit('_'),
        lpad(df['BLOCK_seqnum'].cast('string'),3,'0')
    )
)

paragraphs.title: Calculate some moving totals within each block
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
window_block = Window.partitionBy('BLOCK_id').orderBy('TIME_unix_time')

# Recalculate speed within each block
df = calculate_speed(df, window_block)

# Current total distance in km within the block
df = df.withColumn(
    'DIST_BLOCK_km',
    sum('DIST_diff_meters').over(window_block) / 1000
)

# Current total distance in km within the block
df = df.withColumn(
    'DIST_BLOCK_miles',
    sum('DIST_diff_meters').over(window_block) / 1000 * 0.621371
)

# Current time elapsed in seconds within the block
df = df.withColumn(
    'TIME_BLOCK_elapsed_seconds',
    df['TIME_unix_time'] - first(df['TIME_unix_time']).over(window_block)
)

# Compute rownum within block
df = df.withColumn(
    'BLOCK_rownum',
    (row_number().over(window_block) - 1)   
)

# Compute a scale factor
df = df.withColumn(
    'scaleFactor',
    when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 2048 = 0'),12).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 1024 = 0'),11).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 512 = 0'),10).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 256 = 0'),9).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 128 = 0'),8).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 64 = 0'),7).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 32 = 0'),6).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 16 = 0'),5).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 8 = 0'),4).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 4 = 0'),3).when(expr('BLOCK_rownum % 2 = 0'),2).otherwise(1)
)

paragraphs.title: Tweak some column names and expose as temporary table
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
dff = df.select(
    df['athlete'].alias('ATHLETE'), 
    df['activityName'].alias('ACTIVITY_NAME'), 
    df['activityType'].alias('ACTIVITY_TYPE'),
    df['BLOCK_id'].alias('BLOCK_ID'),
    df['BLOCK_rownum'].alias('BLOCK_ROWNUM'),
    df['scaleFactor'].alias('RESOLUTION_FACTOR'),
    df['time'].alias('POINT_TIME'),
    df['lat'].alias('POINT_LATITUDE'), 
    df['lon'].alias('POINT_LONGITUDE'), 
    df['ele'].alias('POINT_ELEVATION'),
    df['SPEED_kmh'].alias('POINT_SPEED_KMPH'),
    df['SPEED_mph'].alias('POINT_SPEED_MPH'),
    df['heart_rate'].alias('POINT_HR'), 
    df['DIST_bearing'].alias('POINT_BEARING'),
    df['DIST_diff_meters'].alias('POINT_DELTA_METERS'),
    df['TIME_unix_time_diff'].alias('POINT_DELTA_SECONDS'),
    df['DIST_BLOCK_km'].alias('BLOCK_CUMULATIVE_KMS'),
    df['DIST_BLOCK_miles'].alias('BLOCK_CUMULATIVE_MILES'),
    df['TIME_BLOCK_elapsed_seconds'].alias('BLOCK_CUMULATIVE_SECS')
)



dff.createOrReplaceTempView("temp_results")

%md

# Code you can run in ADWC

DROP TABLE ACTIVITIES;

CREATE TABLE "STRAVA"."ACTIVITY_POINTS" 
(
     athlete                    VARCHAR2(100),
     activity_name              VARCHAR2(100),
     activity_type              VARCHAR2(100),
     block_id                   VARCHAR2(100),
     block_rownum              NUMBER,
     resolution_factor         NUMBER,
     point_time                DATE,
     point_latitude            NUMBER,
     point_longitude           NUMBER,
     point_elevation           NUMBER,
     point_speed_kmph          NUMBER,
     point_speed_mph           NUMBER,
     point_hr                  NUMBER,
     point_bearing             NUMBER,
     point_delta_meters        NUMBER,
     point_delta_seconds       NUMBER,
     block_cumulative_kms      NUMBER,
     block_cumulative_miles    NUMBER,
     block_cumulative_secs     NUMBER
);
  
   
set define off
begin
  DBMS_CLOUD.create_credential(
    credential_name => 'OBJ_STORE_CRED',
    username => 'cloud.admin',
    password => 'PASSWORD'
  );
end;
/

begin
 dbms_cloud.copy_data(
    table_name =>'ACTIVITY_POINTS',
    credential_name =>'OBJ_STORE_CRED',
    file_uri_list =>'https://gse00010212.storage.oraclecloud.com/v1/Storage-gse00010212/journeyC/strava/processed/activity_csv/part-00000-742e30a3-54e1-41fb-a941-037caba0f645.csv',
    format => json_object('type' value 'csv', 'ignoremissingcolumns' value 'true', 'dateformat' value 'YYYY-MM-DD\"T\"HH24:MI:SS\"Z\"')
 );
end;
/

select * from user_load_operations;

create table ACTIVITIES as 
select athlete,
   activity_name,
   activity_type,
   min(point_time) activity_start,
   max(point_time) activity_end,
   min(point_latitude) min_latitude,
   max(point_latitude) max_latitude,
   min(point_longitude) min_longitude,
   max(point_longitude) max_longitude,
   min(case when point_time=median_time then point_latitude else null end) median_latitude,
   min(case when point_time=median_time then point_longitude else null end) median_longitude,
   avg(point_speed_mph) avg_mph,
   sum(point_delta_seconds) total_moving_seconds,
   sum(point_delta_meters)/1000 total_moving_kms,
   sum(point_delta_meters)/ 1000 * 0.621371 total_moving_miles,
   count(distinct block_id) num_blocks,
   sum(case when delta_elevation<=0.1 then 0 else delta_elevation end)*3.28084 chg_elevation_ft_approx,
   avg(point_elevation)*3.28084 avg_elevation_ft  ,
   avg(point_hr) average_hr,
   min(hr_95) hr_high,
   min(hr_5) hr_low
from (select a.*,
          point_elevation - lag(point_elevation,1,null) over (partition by athlete, activity_name order by point_time) delta_elevation,
          percentile_disc(0.5) within group (order by point_time) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) median_time,
          percentile_disc(0.05) within group (order by point_hr) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) hr_5,
          percentile_disc(0.95) within group (order by point_hr) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) hr_95
      from activity_points a) aa
group by athlete, activity_name, activity_type
order by activity_start desc;

begin
    DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.EXPLAIN( 
        data_table_name      => 'ACTIVITIES', 
        explain_column_name  => 'AVG_MPH', 
        result_table_name    => 'activity_explain'); 
END; 
/ 
--Display results 
SELECT * FROM activity_explain;

--make a subset ACTIVITIES table based on explain (eliminate some of the redundant columns)
create table activities_ml
as select athlete, activity_name, activity_type, activity_start, avg_mph, total_moving_miles, median_longitude, median_latitude, avg_elevation_ft, total_moving_seconds, num_blocks, chg_elevation_ft_approx, average_hr, hr_high, hr_low
from activities;

drop table activity_explain;
begin
    DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.EXPLAIN( 
        data_table_name      => 'ACTIVITIES_ML', 
        explain_column_name  => 'AVG_MPH', 
        result_table_name    => 'activity_explain'); 
END; 
/ 
--Display results 
SELECT * FROM activity_explain;


--Perform PREDICT operation 
set serveroutput on
DECLARE 
    v_accuracy NUMBER(10,9); 
BEGIN 
    DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.PREDICT( 
        accuracy             => v_accuracy, 
        data_table_name      => 'ACTIVITIES_ML', 
        case_id_column_name  => 'activity_name', 
        target_column_name   => 'avg_mph', 
        result_table_name    => 'activity_predict'); 
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Accuracy = ' || v_accuracy); 
END; 
/

select p.prediction, a.avg_mph, a.* from activity_predict p, activities a
where a.activity_name=p.activity_name;

CREATE or replace VIEW activities_ml_view AS
              SELECT activity_name, to_char(activity_start,'YYYY') activity_year, avg_mph, total_moving_miles, median_longitude, median_latitude, avg_elevation_ft, total_moving_seconds, num_blocks, chg_elevation_ft_approx, average_hr, hr_high, hr_low, activity_type
              FROM activities_ml
              WHERE activity_type!='InlineSkate';
drop table activity_profile;              
BEGIN
    DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.PROFILE(
         DATA_TABLE_NAME    => 'activities_ml_view',
         TARGET_COLUMN_NAME => 'activity_type',
         RESULT_TABLE_NAME  => 'activity_profile');
END;
/

SELECT a.* from activity_profile a;
SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, a.description.getstringval() from activity_profile a;
SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, extract(a.description,'/SimpleRule/CompoundPredicate/SimplePredicate').getstringval() from activity_profile a;

SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, a.description, extract(a.description,'/SimpleRule/CompoundPredicate/SimplePredicate').getstringval()
  FROM activity_profile a
  WHERE extractvalue(a.description, '/SimpleRule/@score') = 'Run';

(

point_speed_mph NUMBER,

begin
dbms_cloud.copy_data(
table_name =>‘ACTIVITY_POINTS’,
credential_name =>‘OBJ_STORE_CRED’,
file_uri_list =>’https://gse00010212.storage.oraclecloud.com/v1/Storage-gse00010212/journeyC/strava/processed/activity_csv/part-00000-742e30a3-54e1-41fb-a941-037caba0f645.csv',

);
end;
/

select * from user_load_operations;

create table ACTIVITIES as
select athlete,
activity_name,
activity_type,
min(point_time) activity_start,
max(point_time) activity_end,
min(point_latitude) min_latitude,
max(point_latitude) max_latitude,
min(point_longitude) min_longitude,
max(point_longitude) max_longitude,
min(case when point_time=median_time then point_latitude else null end) median_latitude,
min(case when point_time=median_time then point_longitude else null end) median_longitude,
avg(point_speed_mph) avg_mph,
sum(point_delta_seconds) total_moving_seconds,
sum(point_delta_meters)/1000 total_moving_kms,
sum(point_delta_meters)/ 1000 * 0.621371 total_moving_miles,
count(distinct block_id) num_blocks,
sum(case when delta_elevation<=0.1 then 0 else delta_elevation end)*3.28084 chg_elevation_ft_approx,
avg(point_elevation)*3.28084 avg_elevation_ft ,
avg(point_hr) average_hr,
min(hr_95) hr_high,
min(hr_5) hr_low
from (select a.*,
point_elevation - lag(point_elevation,1,null) over (partition by athlete, activity_name order by point_time) delta_elevation,
percentile_disc(0.5) within group (order by point_time) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) median_time,
percentile_disc(0.05) within group (order by point_hr) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) hr_5,
percentile_disc(0.95) within group (order by point_hr) over (partition by athlete, activity_name) hr_95
from activity_points a) aa
group by athlete, activity_name, activity_type
order by activity_start desc;

begin
DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.EXPLAIN(
data_table_name => ‘ACTIVITIES’,
explain_column_name => ‘AVG_MPH’,
result_table_name => ‘activity_explain’);
END;
/
–Display results
SELECT * FROM activity_explain;

–make a subset ACTIVITIES table based on explain (eliminate some of the redundant columns)
create table activities_ml
as select athlete, activity_name, activity_type, activity_start, avg_mph, total_moving_miles, median_longitude, median_latitude, avg_elevation_ft, total_moving_seconds, num_blocks, chg_elevation_ft_approx, average_hr, hr_high, hr_low
from activities;

drop table activity_explain;
begin
DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.EXPLAIN(
data_table_name => ‘ACTIVITIES_ML’,
explain_column_name => ‘AVG_MPH’,
result_table_name => ‘activity_explain’);
END;
/
–Display results
SELECT * FROM activity_explain;

–Perform PREDICT operation
set serveroutput on
DECLARE
v_accuracy NUMBER(10,9);
BEGIN
DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.PREDICT(
accuracy => v_accuracy,
data_table_name => ‘ACTIVITIES_ML’,
case_id_column_name => ‘activity_name’,
target_column_name => ‘avg_mph’,
result_table_name => ‘activity_predict’);
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(‘Accuracy = ’ || v_accuracy);
END;
/

select p.prediction, a.avg_mph, a.* from activity_predict p, activities a
where a.activity_name=p.activity_name;

CREATE or replace VIEW activities_ml_view AS
SELECT activity_name, to_char(activity_start,‘YYYY’) activity_year, avg_mph, total_moving_miles, median_longitude, median_latitude, avg_elevation_ft, total_moving_seconds, num_blocks, chg_elevation_ft_approx, average_hr, hr_high, hr_low, activity_type
FROM activities_ml
WHERE activity_type!=‘InlineSkate’;
drop table activity_profile;
BEGIN
DBMS_PREDICTIVE_ANALYTICS.PROFILE(
DATA_TABLE_NAME => ‘activities_ml_view’,
TARGET_COLUMN_NAME => ‘activity_type’,
RESULT_TABLE_NAME => ‘activity_profile’);
END;
/

SELECT a.* from activity_profile a;
SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, a.description.getstringval() from activity_profile a;
SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, extract(a.description,‘/SimpleRule/CompoundPredicate/SimplePredicate’).getstringval() from activity_profile a;

SELECT a.profile_id, a.record_count, a.description, extract(a.description,‘/SimpleRule/CompoundPredicate/SimplePredicate’).getstringval()
FROM activity_profile a
WHERE extractvalue(a.description, ‘/SimpleRule/@score’) = ‘Run’;
